---
alwaysApply: true
---

### Every screen fetches data exclusively through a custom hook.
- No `useEffect` + direct API calls inside screen components.
- No inline fetching in any component file.
- All data logic lives in `src/hooks/`.

### Every custom hook must return this exact shape — no deviations:
```typescript
interface UseQueryResult<T> {
  data: T | null;
  loading: boolean;
  error: string | null;
  refetch: () => void;
}
```

If you generate a hook that returns `isLoading`, `isError`, `errorMessage`, or any other field names — that is wrong. Use exactly `data`, `loading`, `error`, `refetch`.

### All API calls route through `src/api/client.ts`:
- `client.ts` exports a single configured Axios instance.
- It must include:
  - Request interceptor: attaches `Authorization: Bearer {token}` from env vars to every request.
  - Response interceptor: normalises errors to `{ message: string; status: number }`.
  - Retry logic: one automatic retry on network errors (not on 4xx/5xx).
- `src/api/movies.ts` imports the client instance and exports named endpoint functions.
- Hooks import from `src/api/movies.ts` — never from `client.ts` directly and never from `axios` directly.
